<p>Former French culture minister Jack Lang, 86, has offered his resignation as president of the Arab World Institute (IMA), a prominent Paris cultural and research center overseen by France’s foreign ministry, after renewed scrutiny linked to files involving the late financier Jeffrey Epstein. Le Monde and Deutsche Welle reported that Lang’s name appeared 673 times in Epstein-related documents. French prosecutors have opened a financial investigation into suspected laundering of the proceeds of tax fraud. Lang has denied wrongdoing.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/hw3YCV1ah4AbhAOLS0fd8EuMA_viQ-W4YXPVLv-XJ-Z9z-uvV6Er_p8B9KjDPKaqEN3HEpMI98Tv-YO_1_eHkv-B3ivBi9OemrXAQ4BWiCsBTrgeC5kYejbPl9Ul2ZoUTBYUr5J8U5d50lbJ1Yv1skoZJEJi5mfbGyQ89h6iNZ1oCusgbftiR9_gDOYQd1uADx-MRM_Jpj4r7kMvq9_c-MSQHWgQScPaj9UWFr8IR50m9VXGBFdjPGFfg_ESXwdTwQ8' alt='' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Resignation letter: NDTV reported that Lang offered to resign in a letter to the foreign minister seen by AFP.</li><li>Long tenure: Multiple outlets noted that Lang has led the Arab World Institute since 2013 in their coverage of his resignation offer.</li><li>Investigating authority: Japan Today reported that the National Financial Prosecutor’s Office opened the inquiry on Saturday into suspected laundering of tax-fraud proceeds.</li><li>Pressure campaign: Le Monde reported that mentions of Lang in the Epstein documents fueled widespread calls for his immediate departure from the IMA presidency.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Jack Lang: Lang denied wrongdoing and called the probe against him “baseless,” according to Deutsche Welle’s reporting. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/france-ex-minister-jack-lang-resigns-amid-epstein-probe/a-75856210'>DW</a>)</li><li>French National Financial Prosecutor’s Office: The investigation focuses on suspected laundering of tax-fraud proceeds and, in some reporting, names both Lang and his daughter Caroline Lang. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/crkrk567d7zo'>BBC News</a>, <a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/french-justice-opens-epstein-linked-probe-against-former-culture-minister'>Japan Today</a>)</li><li>French foreign ministry: The ministry, which supervises the Arab World Institute, summoned Lang to report on February 8, The Hindu reported. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/france-opens-probe-against-ex-culture-minister-lang-after-epstein-file-dump/article70605451.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2026/02/07/epstein-scandal-prompts-jack-lang-to-offer-resignation-as-head-of-the-world-arab-institute_6750255_4.html'>Epstein scandal prompts Jack Lang to offer resignation as head of the World Arab Institute</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/07/veteran-french-politician-quits-as-head-of-prestigious-institute-after-epstein-links-revealed'>Veteran French politician quits as head of prestigious institute after Epstein links revealed</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch'>France’s former minister Jack Lang ‘offers’ to resign from Arab World Institute over Epstein links</a> - youtube.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/france-opens-probe-against-ex-culture-minister-lang-after-epstein-file-dump/article70605451.ece'>France opens probe against ex-Culture Minister Lang after Epstein file dump</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/crkrk567d7zo'>France investigates ex-minister Jack Lang over Epstein links</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/france-ex-minister-jack-lang-resigns-amid-epstein-probe/a-75856210'>France: Ex-minister Jack Lang resigns amid Epstein probe</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/french-ex-minister-jack-lang-offers-resignation-from-paris-cultural-hub-over-epstein-links'>French ex-minister Jack Lang offers resignat